{
  "texts": [
    "(Right panel) The 2D TN can be contracted directly at the thermodynamic limit using isotropic CTMRG.W W W W W W W W W W W W W W W W W A A C C A C C A FIG.Fig. 4.",
    "In Fig. 4 (right panel), the (A u, A d, A l, A r)'s represent the boundary fixed-point matrix-product state (MPS) tensors, while the C's correspond to the corner transfer matrices (CTMs).",
    "The increased unit-cell size makes the anisotropic CTMRG computationally demanding, and we therefore restrict the MPS bond dimension to χ = 128 for q = 6 for the results shown in the main text.Alternatively, we consider the dual system by defining bond degrees of freedom as σ (i, δ):= θ i -θ i+ δ with δ = x, ŷ [8,9].",
    "The corresponding dual Hamiltonian is given by:H D = -J 1 b cos σ b + J 2 2 ⟨b,b ′ ⟩ cos (σ b + σ b ′),(6)where the bond variables obey the local constraint:cos σ (i,x) + σ (i,ŷ) + σ (i+x,ŷ) + σ (i+ŷ,x) = 1,(7)for each i.",
    "The bond variables σ b take values that are even multiples of π/q, as in the original formulation, with b denoting the bond index."
  ]
